definitions.definition: A small cafeteria or snack bar , especially one in a military establishment, school, or place of work.
examples: He ordered a salad at the canteen .

subdefinitions.definition: A cafeteria in a school or place of work.
Goods purchased from a prison canteen.

definitions.definition: A temporary or mobile café used in an emergency or on a film location etc.
A box with compartments for storing eating utensils , silverware etc.
A water bottle , flask , or other vessel , typically used by a soldier or camper as a bottle for carrying water or liquor for drink
